body:
My take on the XYZ ending: “Sparkling Eyes” Part 2

Back to the main point!

Ok so Kanto! Now we know, Ash Ketchum has never been the, “romantic type”.

I mean Exhibit A..

It was all about pokemon catching, pokemon battles and being a Pokémon master, as it should be; except if you are a girl wanting the guys attention then…..you are out of luck.

The only time Ash has shown any “liking” for a girls was this:

This is child’s play and means absolutely nothing because Ash then defends Misty and her Starmie and bashes this “cute girl” for her style of battling and teaching.

Anywho, back on track! When it comes to girls, Ash is clueless. We already know the only “emotion” Ash has shown when it comes to a girls affection is his jealousy with Misty towards Rudy, Danny, and the dude (forgot his name) when Misty wanted to use Pikachu for a doll contest and finding her cute on multiple occasions with her kimono, goldeen outfit as well as the banned Beauty and the Beach episode.

Other than that, fast forwarding through the Pokegirls, Dawn, May, Iris (defiantly not Iris lol) there hasn’t been any females that have really shown any affection towards Ash other than true friendship and vice versa except for a few travelers and that one psychic Pokemon Battle Frontier leader who REALLY liked Ash

which Ash once again had absolutely no clue.

Now! Enter Serena

This is the first Pokegirl that Pokemon has created that has ever physically (obviously), verbally and emotionally shown her affection towards Ash and boy did she put it on him.

Ash and Serena met when they were kids however, Serena is the only one that remembers. And Ash has been a hero every since he was a little boy because he “saved her” and she has liked him every since.

Years later, she sees Ash on TV in a middle or the end of a battle , I think, it’s been awhile, but she decides to follow her crush all throughout the Kalos region. She is thankful for what he did years ago and tries to display her affection for him and The poor girl did EVERYTHING she could.

Exhibit B and C

Now imagine yourself as Serena, you find your childhood crush after all these years, follow him and meet new friends and Pokémon and when it is time to say goodbye, you realize this is your last chance to share how you feel.

Then there is Ash…face palm. I am a forever Pokeshipper and there is nothing Serena can do to change that but even I felt sorry for her lol. Ash has absolutely no clue or indication that he is aware of her feelings or any signs of showing them back. Because Serena is a sweet girl, Ash was just kind back. That’s it, Nothing to it.

Now to the end!

On to Part 3!
